Download
========

The source code of the version 4 of DIVINE will be made available for download
during summer 2016.  Please also note that DiVinE Cluster, DiVinE Multi-Core
and ProbDiVinE have been discontinued. The 3.x branch of DIVINE is no longer
activaly maintained.

For the time being, you can download [older versions] [2] or contact us if you
would like to contribute to the development of DIVINE 4 (the mainline
repository listed below still points at version 3.x but we will share the
version 4 repository upon request).

Please consult [release notes] [1] for a summary of changes between releases.
Check the [installation instructions] [7] in the manual.

[1]: whatsnew.html
[2]: download

Alternatively, you can obtain the latest source code for DIVINE by fetching it
directly from our version control system, using [darcs] [6]:

    $ darcs get http://divine.fi.muni.cz/darcs/mainline divine

If you experience any problem downloading our source repository please try

    $ darcs get --no-http-pipelining http://divine.fi.muni.cz/darcs/mainline divine

or update to the newest available version of darcs.

[6]: http://darcs.net
[7]: manual.html#installation
